Package: sub
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Subhadip Sarkar <sarkarsubhadip604@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 11331
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8)
Recommends: gcc, rustc, default-jdk, nmap, whois, dnsutils, traceroute, nasm, m4
Suggests: kotlinc, nvcc
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/subhobhai943/sub
Description: Polyglot hacking & utility CLI tool
 sub is a multi-backend command-line toolkit written in Python, C, Rust,
 Kotlin, Java, Haxe, CUDA C++, Assembly (x86_64/aarch64), and M4.
 .
 A single bash dispatcher routes each command to the fastest available
 native backend, with graceful fallback to Python.
 .
 Commands: whoami, sysinfo, info, myip, scan, ports, subdomain,
 banner-grab, geoip, rdns, ifaces, traceroute, dns, whois, ipinfo,
 ping, headers, netstat, hashid, pwcheck, caesar, b64, hash, encode,
 generate, weather, myrepos, gpuinfo, m4, version.
 .
 GitHub: https://github.com/subhobhai943/sub
